<title>UK: British Gas Q3 historic net loss widens.</title>
<headline>British Gas Q3 historic net loss widens.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-11-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Third quarter to September 30</p>
<p>			   (million stg unless stated)</p>
<p> Shr (pence)		8.3 loss	     vs 4.1 loss</p>
<p> Historic cost net	364 loss	     vs 181 loss</p>
<p> Current cost net	 480 loss	     vs 274 loss</p>
<p> Turnover		   1.43 billion	 vs 1.11 billion</p>
<p>NOTE - Analysts' forecasts on historic cost net loss were in a range of 150 to 128 million stg.  </p>
<p> Exceptional charges    304		    vs nil</p>
<p> Pretax		     501 loss	     vs 282 loss</p>
<p> Hist. cost operating   478 loss	     vs 264 loss</p>
<p>Breakdown historical cost operating result pre exceptional charges:</p>
<p> TransCo		    88  profit	   vs 3 loss</p>
<p> Trading		    286 loss	     vs 285 loss</p>
<p> Exploration and production 30		 vs 23</p>
<p> Other			6 loss		 vs 1 profit</p>
<p>Breakdown execptional charges:</p>
<p> Sales contract provisions 294		 vs nil</p>
<p> Demerger costs	  10			vs nil</p>
